text.text:
Building tools to enable capacity in Google Cloud to quickly, safely, and automatically move to prevent stockouts and maximize efficiency.

Design and implementation of a system that automates the movement of SSD capacity between GCE and the rest of Google to maximize utilization and improve efficiency of SSD disks.

Designed and implemented systems that allow VMs to be scheduled at the best possible hardware, which optimizes performance while increasing efficiency and reliability.

text.text:
Part of Google Compute Engine (GCE) and keeping GCE VMs running by managing their underlying infrastructure. Mostly writing Go or Python and helping GCP Persistent Disk (PD) and Local SSD products to server customers at Google hyper-scale.

Implementation of the system that optimizes the usage of SSD disks in the GCE fleet to guarantee different demands are met at any moment in time.

text.text:
After the MapR acquisition by HPE, I continue to work using the MapR Data Platform to help our customers to design, implement, and deploy BigData solutions on top of the MapR Data Platform HPE Container Platform.  

Daily routines include heavily coding in Scala or Java, use of Apache Spark, MapR Streams, MapR-DB, and other components for Big Data to ultimately help our customers succeed in their journey to data processing at scale.

Committer to internal MapR Spark implementation by adding optimized functionality to access MapR-Database and newest Kafka and MapR-ES APIs.

Contributions to Apache Drill via Custom Storage Plugins implementations for customer indexing systems on top of MapR-Database - shorturl.at/GQT06

Contributor to the following MapR tools:
- akka-persistence-maprdb (https://github.com/anicolaspp/akka-persistence-maprdb)
- akka-streams-alpakka-maprdb (https://github.com/anicolaspp/akka-streams-alpakka-maprdb)

text.text:
Engineering of core micro-services for Royal Caribbean Cruises (RCCL) web and mobile systems that allow multiple core systems on the RCCL to run in the ships even though ship connectivity is low and many time non-existent. For instance, the micro-services for managing data streaming and replication from/to the cruises in a reactive and distributed manner. All of these systems use the Lightbend Reactive Platform, Lagom, Play framework, Kafka and Confluent Kafka Connect, and Cassandra.

Additionally, also worked on a set of micro-services that expose Commerce APIs to the different Royal Caribbean Mobile Apps so that customer can access multiple services during the trip and while oversea when there is no connectivity and the ship works as a datacenter itself which is quite challenging, specially for payment related operations.

text.text:
Part of Big Data team that enables information access at scale by building Big Data Pipelines using Amazon technologies to enable access to Subway POS payment information which allows access to previously unknown insights about customer activities. 

Using AWS BigData core technologies such as AWS S3, Data Pipelines, EMR, Redshift, DynamoDB alongside with Scala, and Apache Spark to build the end to end pipelines processing the related payment information from the Subway POS.
